How to install patches from this directory

First of all make sure, that gnublin_SP1 patch is installed.The gnublin_SP1 patch is essential for booting the Gnublin Board!
Then please make a Backup of your .config file! 

You can install the patches by changing to the kernel directory (linux-2.6.33-lpc313x) and typing the following:



patch -p2 < ./../patches/<patch_you_want_to_install>





The best method for installing the patches is to run  the *install_patches.sh* 
*************************************************************************************

If you want to install your own patches the first sign of the patchname has to be a zero:

0[your_patchname].patch

The diff command for creating patches has to be run is this directory!!!
